# `.claude/settings.local.json` is commonly excluded by a global git ignore
# (e.g. ~/.config/git/ignore has `**/.claude/settings.local.json`). This profile
# intentionally SHIPS that file as a template — templates/.claude/settings.local.json
# pre-approves the CodeScene MCP for scaffolded projects — so re-include it here and
# keep it tracked. Without this negation it silently never gets committed.
!templates/.claude/settings.local.json
